{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C.","Place sugar in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Set scales to zero then, using a spoon, remove 10 g ground sugar (scales will show -10 g) and reserve.","Add flour and salt (if using) then aerate <nobr>30 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla sugar (see tip) in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, whip <nobr>4 min\/50°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>.","Still without measuring cup, whip again <nobr>4-6 min\/50°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr> while slowly adding reserved ground sugar, 1 Tbsp at a time, through hole in mixing bowl lid until soft peaks form.","Add beaten egg whites to reserved flour and gently fold in with spatula.","Transfer mixture to an angel food cake tin (Ø 23-25 cm) and bake immediately for 35-40 minutes (180°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean and cracks appear dry. Invert tin and leave to cool completely (approx. 3 hours). Once cool, unmould onto a serving plate and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["280 g sugar","125 g cake flour","¼ tsp fine sea salt              (optional)","10 egg whites, from medium eggs, room temperature","1 ½ tsp cream of tartar","1 tsp vanilla sugar, homemade (see tip)"]}],"id":"r400908","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-N4qjHJfEpuM\/XZWraduoVyI\/AAAAAAAAfnA\/9bee3VShPCgNK4Dg5ucZ2GdsCBkh8r3UgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ksGVFLBbX9cjYwXn.png","title":"Angel Food Cake","publishedAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"626 kJ \/ 150 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, angel food cake tin (Ø 23-25 cm), skewer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Angel Food Cake leftovers can be used for the cake base of trifles.","Cakes are at their best when consumed within one day. To prevent them from drying out, store in a container in the fridge. Angel Food Cake will keep for <nobr>4-5 days<\/nobr> in the fridge or up to <nobr>1 month<\/nobr> in the freezer.","To make your own vanilla sugar before you start the recipe, follow the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 10m","12 slices"]}